<div>
	<h1>Revolutionary Biology</h1>
<div class="image_container right" style="width: 200px;"><img src="/_asset/image/revolutionary-biology.png/fit/200/200" alt="Revolutionary biology" />
<div class="image_sub_text">A scene from Episode 1, 'The building blocks of life'</div>
</div>
<p>2014 is the International Year of Crystallography and to celebrate this anniversary NDM has produced a series of short films entitled <em>Revolutionary Biology</em>.</p>
<p>The series shows how the field of structural biology has developed over the past 100 years, Oxford&rsquo;s involvement in that development, and where we go from here.</p>
<p>The videos will be released on Tuesdays over the coming weeks, with the first video in this series, '<a href="http://www.ndm.ox.ac.uk/part-1-the-building-blocks-of-life" target="_self">The building blocks of life</a>', available to watch from 10am on Tuesday 21 October.</p>
<p>NDM Head of Operations Karen Valentine says 'We hope that you enjoy watching how NDM and Oxford scientists have had a major role in revolutionising drug discovery.'</p></div>
